    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>tofu</strong> into bite-sized chunks</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to a large bowl with<strong> </strong>your <strong>ground paprika</strong>, <strong>umami seasoning</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> pepper </strong>and give it a good mix up</p><p>Add the<strong> torn tofu</strong> and toss until everything is well coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sweet-n-sour-tofu-and-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated tofu</strong> (reserve the bowl!) and cook for 12-15 min until golden and crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sweet-n-sour-tofu-and-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml] </span>cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sweet-n-sour-tofu-and-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into squares</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>into wedges, then into squares</p><p>Remove your <strong>pineapple</strong> from the can (save the juice!) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sweet-n-sour-tofu-and-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> tomato ketchup</strong>,<strong> ginger paste </strong>and<strong> remaining soy sauce </strong>in a bowl with the <strong>reserved pineapple juice </strong>and<strong> </strong>your <strong>rice vinegar</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013this is your <strong>sweet 'N' sour sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sweet-n-sour-tofu-and-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu is crispy, transfer the <strong>crispy tofu</strong> to a plate and set aside, reserving the pan</p><p>Wipe clean the reserved pan and return it to a high heat with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>pepper </strong>and <strong>pineapple</strong> and cook for 4-6 min or until softened and slightly charred</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sweet-n-sour-tofu-and-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>on the diagonal</p><p>Once the veg is softened and slightly charred, add the <strong>sweet 'N' sour sauce </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add the <strong>crispy tofu </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>sweet 'N' sour tofu with pepper & pineapple</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sweet-n-sour-tofu-and-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet 'N' sour tofu with pepper & pineapple </strong>with the <strong>cooked rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
